        <h2>Nutritional Profile üí™</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Vitamins:</strong> High in Vitamin A, C, E, and B-complex</li>
            <li><strong>Minerals:</strong> Rich in calcium, iron, magnesium, potassium, and zinc</li>
            <li><strong>Protein:</strong> Contains all nine essential amino acids</li>
            <li><strong>Antioxidants:</strong> High levels of quercetin, chlorogenic acid, and beta-carotene</li>
            <li><strong>Healthy Fats:</strong> Seeds are rich in oleic acid, similar to olive oil</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Health Benefits of Moringa</h2>

        <div class="card">
            <h3>1. Packed with Antioxidants & Anti-Inflammatory Properties üî•</h3>
            <p>Moringa leaves contain powerful antioxidants like quercetin and chlorogenic acid, which help reduce oxidative stress, neutralizing harmful free radicals in the body. Its natural anti-inflammatory properties help alleviate conditions like arthritis, asthma, and chronic pain.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h3>2. Supports Heart Health ‚ù§Ô∏è</h3>
            <ul>
