                <li>Regulates blood pressure with high potassium content</li>
                <li>Improves circulation and cardiovascular function</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
        <h3>3. Boosts the Immune System üåø</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Contains seven times more Vitamin C than oranges</li>
            <li>Supports white blood cell production</li>
            <li>Antimicrobial properties combat bacteria and viruses</li>
        </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
        <h3>4. Enhances Brain Function üß†</h3>
        <p>Moringa contains neuroprotective compounds that enhance memory, cognitive function, and mood stability. Its high antioxidant levels help protect neurons from oxidative damage, potentially reducing the risk of Alzheimer‚Äôs and dementia.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
        <h3>5. Supports Healthy Skin and Hair </h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Vitamin E and A promote healthy skin, reduce wrinkles, and fight acne</li>
            <li>Collagen production is enhanced by its high Vitamin C content/li>
            <li>Strengthens hair follicles, reducing hair loss and improving scalp health</li>
        </ul>
        </div>
