                <li>Moringa has hepatoprotective properties, meaning it protects the liver from toxins.</li>
                <li>Helps cleanse the body from heavy metals and environmental pollutants.</li>
                <li>Supports healthy kidney and liver function.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    
        <h2>How to Use Moringa</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Fresh Leaves:</strong> Eaten raw, in salads, or cooked like spinach.</li>
            <li><strong>Powder:</strong> Added to smoothies, teas, and soups.</li>
            <li><strong>Capsules:</strong> Convenient for supplementation.</li>
            <li><strong>Seeds:</strong> Used for water purification or eaten roasted.</li>
            <li><strong>Oil (Ben Oil):</strong> Applied for skin care and cooking.</li>
        </ul>

